      • from

        public static FsHttpHeaders from(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,?> map)
        Returns headers of which content from given map.

        If a value is instance of Collection, it will be considered as repeated header and converts to List<String> by String.valueOf(Object) for each element, then add into the associated key. This method is equivalent to: 

             FsHttpHeaders headers = new FsHttpHeaders();
     headers.addHeaders(map);
     return headers;
        See addHeader(String, Object).
        Parameters:
        map - given map
        Returns:
        headers of which content from given map
        See Also:
        addHeaders(Map)

      • addHeaders

        public FsHttpHeaders addHeaders(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,?> headers)
        Adds headers.

        If a value is instance of Collection, it will be considered as repeated header and converts to List<String> by String.valueOf(Object) for each element, then add into the associated key. This method is equivalent to: 

             headers.forEach(this::addHeader);
        See addHeader(String, Object).
        Parameters:
        headers - headers to be added
        Returns:
        this headers
        See Also:
        addHeader(String, Object)
